# Contributor: Sheila Aman <sheila@vulpine.house>
# Maintainer: Natanael Copa <ncopa@alpinelinux.org>
#
# --- Nexus Q (steelhead) local override of Alpine's main/python3 --------------
# Alpine's stock python3-3.14.5-r2 SIGSEGVs deterministically on armv7 (Cortex-A9)
# on the very first bytecode -- even `python3 -S -c ''` crashes (rc 139). That
# takes down every python consumer on the device (sleep-inhibitor.service, onboard,
# blueman-applet).
#
# This rebuild (started r3, now r4) drops LTO + PGO at a higher pkgrel so it is meant
# to supersede Alpine's -r2 in the rootfs. (PGO also cannot run in our qemu armv7
# build at all -- it would execute an instrumented interpreter under qemu.)
#
# !!! STATUS 2026-06-28: NOT YET A WORKING FIX -- OPEN. Narrowed to a CPython 3.14
# SOURCE-level use-before-init / garbage-pointer read, NOT a compiler problem. During
# Py_Initialize, _PyStaticType_InitBuiltin reads a garbage type-index
# (interp->types.builtins.num_initialized = 0xf0012b00) and derefs a wild address
# (_PyRuntime.types.managed_static.types[idx]); that address is UNMAPPED on real
# hardware (SIGSEGV) but mapped under qemu-user (FALSE PASS).
# DISPROVEN, with evidence -- do NOT re-tread:
#   - LTO/PGO: r3 dropped both, still crashes.
#   - LDREXD misalignment: coredump faulting addr is 8-byte aligned but UNMAPPED
#     (SIGSEGV, not SIGBUS) -- the bad ADDRESS, not its alignment.
#   - gnu2/TLSDESC: binary uses traditional TLS (__tls_get_addr, 0 R_ARM_TLS_DESC).
#   - optimization level itself: two -O0 r4 builds with BYTE-IDENTICAL .text
#     (3,528,976 bytes, cmp-equal) differing only in ~139 KB of data behave
#     oppositely on the same device -> data/layout-dependent, not codegen.
# So no -O/-f flag fixes this; the fix is source/upstream (candidate 3.14.6). The -O0
# in build() below is the current experiment state, NOT the fix. ALWAYS validate
# `python3 -S -c ''` ON THE DEVICE, never on the qemu chroot. Drop this override once
# Alpine (or upstream CPython) ships a working armv7 python.
# See docs/2026-06-28-session-findings.md.
#
# One further deviation from Alpine's stock APKBUILD: the makedepends no longer
# carries the `!gettext-dev` conflict token. abuild understands `!pkg` (ensure it
# is NOT installed), but pmbootstrap pre-installs makedepends with its own apk
# wrapper, which rejects any `!`-prefixed entry ("packages with '!' are not
# supported!") -- so Phase 7d cannot build python3 with it present. The token is a
# no-op guard here anyway: nothing in this makedepends closure pulls gettext-dev,
# and musl-libintl is listed explicitly, so the build result is unchanged.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pkgname=python3
# python3-extra's pkgver needs to be synchronized with this.
pkgver=3.14.5
_basever="${pkgver%.*}"
pkgrel=4
pkgdesc="High-level scripting language"
url="https://www.python.org/"
arch="all"
license="PSF-2.0"
# pyc0 comes last because the files are named without a unique substring
subpackages="
	$pkgname-dbg
	$pkgname-dev
	$pkgname-doc
	$pkgname-idle::noarch
	$pkgname-tests::noarch
	$pkgname-pyc:_default_pyc
	$pkgname-pycache-pyc2
	$pkgname-pycache-pyc1
	$pkgname-pycache-pyc0
	pyc:_pyc_meta:noarch
	"
depends="libssl3>=3.3.0"
makedepends="
	bluez-headers
	bzip2-dev
	expat-dev
	libffi-dev
	linux-headers
	mpdecimal-dev
	musl-libintl
	ncurses-dev
	openssl-dev
	readline-dev
	sqlite-dev
	tcl-dev
	xz-dev
	zlib-dev
	"
source="https://www.python.org/ftp/python/$pkgver/Python-$pkgver.tar.xz
	idle.desktop
	externally-managed
	musl-find_library.patch
	s390x-c-stack-size.patch
	"
# net: the source tarball is fetched during build.
# !check: skip the upstream test suite -- it is extremely slow and can hang under
# qemu armv7 emulation; we gate correctness on `python3 -S -c ''` (rc 0) instead.
options="net !check" # Required for tests
builddir="$srcdir/Python-$pkgver"

